import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['source'], bins='auto', color='blue', alpha=0.7, rwidth=0.85)
    plt.xlabel('Source Nodes')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of source nodes in the Flare Dependencies Dataset?', wrap=True)
    plt.grid(axis='y', alpha=0.75)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['target'], bins='auto', color='blue', alpha=0.7, rwidth=0.85)
    plt.xlabel('Target Nodes')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of target nodes in the Flare Dependencies Dataset?', wrap=True)
    plt.grid(axis='y', alpha=0.75)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    scatter = ax.scatter(data['source'], data['target'], c=data['source'], cmap='viridis')
    plt.xlabel('Source Nodes')
    plt.ylabel('Target Nodes')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between source and target nodes in the Flare Dependencies Dataset?', wrap=True)
    legend1 = ax.legend(*scatter.legend_elements(), title="Source Nodes")
    ax.add_artist(legend1)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    source_counts = data['source'].value_counts().head(10)
    ax = source_counts.plot(kind='bar', color='c', legend=True)
    plt.title('What is the most common source node in the Flare Dependencies Dataset?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Source Node')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    most_common_source = source_counts.index[0]
    plt.axvline(x=most_common_source, color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Most Common Source: {most_common_source:.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
